  <title>Gio.BufferedOutputStream</title>
  <synopsis><code>
const Gio = imports.gi.Gio;

let bufferedOutputStream = new Gio.BufferedOutputStream({
    <link xref='Gio.BufferedOutputStream-buffer-size'>buffer_size</link>: value,
});
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Buffered output stream implements <link xref="Gio.FilterOutputStream"/> and provides
for buffered writes.</p>  <p>By default, <link xref="Gio.BufferedOutputStream"/>'s buffer size is set at 4 kilobytes.</p>  <p>To create a buffered output stream, use <link xref="Gio.new"/>,
or <link xref="Gio.new_sized"/> to specify the buffer's size
at construction.</p>  <p>To get the size of a buffer within a buffered input stream, use
<link xref="Gio.get_buffer_size"/>. To change the size of a
buffered output stream's buffer, use
<link xref="Gio.set_buffer_size"/>. Note that the buffer's
size cannot be reduced below the size of the data within the buffer.</p>

